[ProMED-mail thanks Dr. Berger for this information. Since _C.
perfringens_ elaborates its enterotoxin in situ in the
gastrointestinal tract, unlike _S. aureus_, the isolation of the
organism in diarrheal stool is helpful in making a diagnosis. -
Mod.LL]
